[SN]TITLE[SN]
Mark Reddish: Harlequins sign New Zealand second row for 2016-17 season

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Premiership club Harlequins have added New Zealand-born second row Mark Reddish to their squad for next season.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Reddish, 31, currently plays for Super Rugby side Otago Highlanders but will join Quins in the autumn.
He has made more than 50 Super Rugby appearances since 2011 and has also represented New Zealand Barbarians.
"Mark's physical and uncompromising style will make him an invaluable part of the squad," Harlequins director of rugby John Kingston said.
